snippet.title: Woman dies in dog attack at Perth kennel
snippet.content: A woman has died after being attacked by a dog at a boarding kennel in Perth's south. The woman, aged in her 50s, was pronounced dead by paramedics after police were called to a Southern River property about 1.30pm on Tuesday. City of Gosnells rangers have seized the dog while a report is being prepared for the coroner. Originally published as
